# Global Alignment (No Drift)

## Source of Truth

`AGENTS.md` at the repo root is the **only** rulebook. Cursor rules, Qoder rules, Kiro agent config, and skills must **mirror** it — never invent conflicting policy.

**Two layers:** Product monorepo (`apps/`, `packages/`) is standalone — never depends on Agentic AI content (`.cursor/`, `pnpm ai`) at runtime or in product quality gates. Contract: `.cursor/standards/layer-boundary/STANDARD.md`.

| Layer | Role |
|---|---|
| `AGENTS.md` | Canonical policy |
| `.cursor/rules/` | Cursor always-on enforcement |
| `.cursor/rules/01-real-world-logic.mdc` | Evidence-based reasoning, no speculation-as-fact |
| `.cursor/rules/02-agent-scoring.mdc` | Alignment scoring gate (≥ 80 per AGENTS.md) |
| `.cursor/rules/03-stack-hard-gates.mdc` | Hard technology/monorepo gates (pnpm, AppError, Zod) |
| `.cursor/rules/04-subagent-auto-routing.mdc` | Mandatory Task/subagent delegation |
| `.cursor/rules/05-portal-dev-keepalive.mdc` | Portal `:3000` up after task batches; restart / fix-retry |
| `.cursor/rules/06-ai-maintenance-background.mdc` | Background `ai-maintenance-checker` + `pnpm ai` |
| `.cursor/rules/07-adaptive-skill-loop.mdc` | Hermes-style distill/patch + progressive disclosure |
| `.cursor/rules/08-agent-communication-delegation.mdc` | Agent communication, context sharing, asset handling |
| `.cursor/rules/09-ai-surface-layout.mdc` | Skills/agents/hooks Anthropic layout enforcement |
| `.cursor/rules/10-orchestrator-patterns.mdc` | Orchestrator patterns for multi-agent workflows |
| `.cursor/rules/11-permanent-fixes.mdc` | Permanent & complete fixes verified on real-world data |
| `.cursor/rules/12-skill-evolution-notifications.mdc` | Self-learning skill evolution reporting protocol |
| `.cursor/rules/harness.mdc` | Optional data-intensive harness sidecar (AGENTS.md wins) |
| `.cursor/agents/` | Project specialists (auto-routed) |
| `.qoder/rules/` | Qoder mirror |
| `.kiro/agents/default.json` | Machine-readable gates |
| `.cursor/skills/agent-alignment-score/` | Score before "done" |

## Drift Ban

- Do not soften, reinterpret, or "optimize past" AGENTS.md §18 never-dos.
- Do not invent alternate stacks (Never use npm or yarn — pnpm 9 only; no new UI kits / state libs) without design-phase approval.
- If a local rule conflicts with AGENTS.md → **AGENTS.md wins**. Flag the conflict; do not silently diverge.
- Multi-file work → `.kiro/specs/<feature-slug>/` phases before implementation.

## Pre-Flight (every non-trivial task)

1. Restate intent in one line (real-world outcome, not tool theater).
2. Count files likely touched. If >1 → require/create specs.
3. Name the AGENTS.md sections that apply (§1–§19).
4. Plan verification evidence (`pnpm quality`, `pnpm ai check` when AI surfaces change, tests, runtime check) before coding.

## Mandatory Reflection Phase

- Before marking any non-trivial task as done, you MUST invoke `pnpm agent:delegate reflection <context>`.
- Log any identified mistakes in `gap-ledger.md` and trigger `skill-self-improve` if the gap is repeatable.
